1. Set Permissions: chmod

chmod 644 filename

→ Sets permissions:

Owner → read + write (rw-)

Group → read-only (r--)

Others → read-only (r--)

2. Add Execute Permission to Owner: chmod

chmod u+x filename

3. Change File Owner: chown

chown newowner filename

→ Changes the file owner to newowner.

4. Change File Group: chgrp

chgrp newgroup filename

→ Changes the file group to newgroup.

5. Set Directory Permissions: chmod

chmod 755 filename

→ Sets permissions:
Owner → read + write + execute (rwx)

Group → read + execute (r-x)

Others → read + execute (r-x)
